<subSubSection pageNumber="655" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="655">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="655">Note:</emphasis>
<specimenReference collectionCode="LINN" specimenCode="276.1">
Herb. Linn. 276.1 (
<collectionCode>LINN</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
has been indicated as the type by a number of authors since Fawcett &amp; Rendle (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="655">Fl. Jamaica</emphasis>
5: 7. 1926), but it is evidently a later addition to the herbarium and not original material for the name. Although Mukherji (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="655">Lloydia</emphasis>
12: 74, 83. 1949) concluded that no type specimen existed, he treated 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hermann’s">Hermann's</normalizedToken>
description as the basis of the species (which is contrary to Art. 8.1). Kostermans &amp; Bompard (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="655">The Mangoes</emphasis>
: 96, f. 61. 1993) treated an illustration in 
<specimenReference collectionCode="BM" specimenCode="223">
Herb. Hermann 5: 223 (
<collectionCode>BM</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
as the 
<typeStatus>holotype</typeStatus>
, but their choice is pre-dated by that of Bornstein, which is accepted here.
</paragraph>
